# Pass B: External Lexicon Merge Prompt
# Purpose: Augment Abbott-Smith base data with additional Hellenistic (300 BCE–300 CE) attestations
# from public-domain lexicons and grammars; paraphrase restricted sources. No sense creation yet.

## INPUT
Lemma: {{lemma}}
Base JSON (from Pass A):
{{base_json}}

## TASK
Produce JSON adding external attestations and usage evidence for {{lemma}} limited to Hellenistic period (300 BCE–300 CE). Do NOT invent references. Do NOT classify senses. Do NOT add "Demonstrative Pronoun" usage for ὁ or αὐτός. Focus on raw usage expansion.

## ALLOWED PUBLIC-DOMAIN SOURCES (verbatim short snippets permitted if certain):
- Abbott-Smith (already in base)
- Moulton & Milligan (MM)
- LSJ (core + Revised Supplement)
- Robertson (Rob)
- Blass-Debrunner-Funk (BDF) – brief clause, not page-long
- Moulton-Howard-Turner (MHT) – brief clause
- Mayser (Mayser)
- Gignac (Gignac)
- Smyth (Smyth)

## RESTRICTED (PARAPHRASE ONLY, NO VERBATIM):
- BDAG
- Brill / Montanari
- Lampe
Mark paraphrased items paraphrase: true.

## SOURCE TYPES
Use one of:
- "NT" (Canonical New Testament)
- "LXX" (Greek OT books in Koine style)
- "papyri" (documentary P.Oxy., P.Tebt., P.Flor., P.Mich., PSI, etc.)
- "inscription" (IG, OGIS, SEG, SIG)
- "literary" (Philo, Josephus, Polybius, Plutarch if within range)
- "patristic" (ONLY 2nd–3rd c. CE early usage; exclude later)
- "grammar-citation" (functions from grammars; supply minimal phrase if present)

Exclude purely Classical (Homer, 5th c. BCE Attic) unless re-attested in Hellenistic prose or documentary sources.

## DATE HANDLING
Provide either numeric year range (e.g. -250, 50) or approximate:
- dateFrom (int, negative for BCE)
- dateTo (int)
If unknown but safely within Hellenistic period use null; do not guess outside range.

## QUOTATION RULES
- Only quote verbatim if certain and from allowed source.
- Never quote restricted sources; paraphrase instead.
- If uncertain about verbatim accuracy, paraphrase and set paraphrase: true.

## EMPHATIC / FUNCTION WORD NOTE
For function words (articles, particles, pronouns, prepositions, conjunctions):
- Capture usage illustrating discourse/pragmatic roles (emphasis, contrast, focus, topic shift, nominalization).
- Do NOT create senses; just record as usage notes.
- Historical demonstrative function for ὁ / αὐτός not productive: if encountered, record under nonProductive: true in notes array.

## OUTPUT SCHEMA (STRICT)
{
  "lemma": "string",
  "externalUsages": [
    {
      "source": "string",                // e.g. "MM", "LSJ", "P.Oxy.", "Luke"
      "ref": "string|null",              // e.g. "Luke 5:37", "P.Oxy. 1234.5-7"
      "form": "string|null",             // Greek form or minimal phrase
      "snippet": "string|null",          // verbatim or paraphrase short snippet
      "translation": "string|null",      // idiomatic English (if form given)
      "sourceType": "NT|LXX|papyri|inscription|literary|patristic|grammar-citation",
      "paraphrase": true|false,
      "dateFrom": number|null,
      "dateTo": number|null,
      "register": "string|null",         // e.g. "contract", "petition", "narrative", "theological", "letter"
      "functionHint": "string|null",     // e.g. "emphatic self-reference", "contrast marker", "nominalized participle"
      "note": "string|null"              // extra clarifying note
    }
  ],
  "structuralPatterns": [
    {
      "pattern": "string",               // e.g. "article + adjective + noun"
      "example": "string|null",          // Greek pattern sample
      "translation": "string|null",
      "note": "string|null",
      "nonProductive": true|false
    }
  ],
  "historicalFlags": [
    "string"                             // e.g. "Demonstrative origin not productive"
  ],
  "warnings": [
    "string"
  ]
}

## RULES
1. Preserve lemma exactly.
2. Max entries: up to 30 usages if available; prioritize diversity (NT, papyri, inscriptions, literary).
3. Prefer documentary (papyri/inscriptions) where multiple choices exist for the same function.
4. No invented refs (must be attested widely; if uncertain, omit).
5. If base already contains a citation, you may include again ONLY if adding new metadata (register, functionHint).
6. structuralPatterns: record positions (e.g. double article pattern) but mark nonProductive: false unless specifically historical only.
7. For ὁ / αὐτός: add to historicalFlags: "No demonstrative pronoun sense (non-productive in Koiné)."
8. Warnings list any dropped ambiguous or out-of-range items.

## VALIDATION (INTERNAL—DO NOT OUTPUT)
- All sourceType values valid.
- No demonstrative sense promoted.
- Dates within -300 to 300 or null.
- paraphrase true for restricted sources.

## OUTPUT
Return ONLY the JSON object. No commentary, no Markdown.

If no external usages found:
{
  "lemma": "{{lemma}}",
  "externalUsages": [],
  "structuralPatterns": [],
  "historicalFlags": [],
  "warnings": ["No additional Hellenistic usages located."]
}